message.content: There is 1 part acid to 2 parts of the solution that is not acid, or "pure water."  So, we have $20$ ounces acid to $80$ ounces pure water.  To get from 30 ounces of a 30% solution to a 20% solution, we take away $10$ ounces acid and $10$ ounces water.  We are left with $\boxed{70}$ ounces of water.
